Week 5 of NFL QB DICK Size... Scoring each QB by aDOT and Passing TDs. 

Updates:
- Dot sizes represent pass attempts
- Team colors
- Andy Dalton officially filtered out

Data: #nflverse https://t.co/vFxJ0NcjfO

Which RBs are expected to increase their red zone TD total this season?

*One thing to note is that, yes, Jalen Hurts has 10 rush attempts in the red zone.

Also, this is definitely not a Jonathan Taylor tweet. Nope. Not one bit.

#nflverse https://t.co/os0Oma4hWO

We're through 5 weeks and maybe the @steelers are showing signs of life!  Well, at least in my eyes - to my model, things are still pretty grim. See the end of season projections, & marvel at the @Chiefs, a team that my model thinks is foundational...meh.  We'll see!  #nflverse https://t.co/2zq0HR3AuR https://t.co/mxApsm4gkz

Week 6 game predictions - remember, the model doesn't know anything about injuries or fundamental changes (Gruden), but should "learn" relatively quickly from the games played in that environment, so will be interesting to see how @Broncos and the @Seahawks fare #nflverse https://t.co/pLoibdnyx5

And two new features this week - projected team wins and playoff probabilities over time - track your favorite team's rising and falling stock through their dynamic end of year projections #nflverse https://t.co/9icTO55Tpn
#nflverse data are for all and explicitly not only for R users! https://t.co/gjmN3wpjI6
@CowboysStats the biggest philadelphia eagles fan in the #nflverse, @CowboysStats and graphics
@danmorse_ Excited to announce that @danmorse_ and I will be the first paid contributors to @nflversetweets. #nflverse

KFL analysis will be on light side (only wk recaps) for the next few weeks as I work on a Shiny R website for the league. Will have all time records, H2H results and the ability to download your historical records against any opponent. Any suggestions? #KFL #ffverse #nflverse https://t.co/dKFDjsTZA7
